The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Jamia suspends suspects
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Jamia suspends suspects
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	New Delhi, Sept. 22: Delhis Jamia Millia Islamia has accepted that two of the men arrested for suspected terror links are its students and suspended them based on prima facie details provided by police today.         
	Zia-ur Rahman and Mohammed Shakeel  arrested yesterday  are registered as students of the universitys BA programme and MA (economics) course, respectively, Jamia officials confirmed.         
	This is the first time a central university in India has suspended students for alleged terror links, University Grants Commission officials said.         
	Yes, I can confirm that the two boys are registered students at Jamia. But we have suspended them based on the prima facie information provided by the police, Jamia vice-chancellor Mushirul Hasan said.         
	Hasan added the university would initiate disciplinary proceedings against the two tomorrow.         
	The police had claimed that a third man arrested yesterday, Saqib Nissar, was a distance-education MBA student at Sikkim Manipal University. SMU chief executive officer Anand Sudarshan refused to confirm or deny the claim. But other SMU sources indicated the university database had thrown up a Saqib whose details matched those provided by the police.                                                                                                                                                                         
